    "plan_content": "Here's a summary of the plan I've prepared:\n\n## Plan: Add `next/geo` Utility Module\n\n### What I found by exploring the codebase\n\nThe existing `next/server` module follows a three-file pattern I'll replicate exactly:\n- **Implementation** in `src/server/web/spec-extension/user-agent.ts` â€” defines interface + exports named functions\n- **CJS entry point** `server.js` â€” `const obj = { require(...) }`, then `module.exports = obj` + individual `exports.X = obj.X`\n- **Type declarations** `server.d.ts` â€” `export { X } from 'next/dist/...'` re-exports\n\nTests use Jest (`describe`/`it`/`expect`), confirmed by `adapters/headers.test.ts`.\n\n### 5 files to create/modify\n\n| Action | File |\n|--------|------|\n| **Create** | `packages/next/src/server/web/spec-extension/geo.ts` |\n| **Create** | `packages/next/geo.js` |\n| **Create** | `packages/next/geo.d.ts` |\n| **Create** | `packages/next/src/server/web/spec-extension/geo.test.ts` |\n| **Modify** | `packages/next/package.json` â€” add `\"geo.js\"`, `\"geo.d.ts\"` after `\"form.d.ts\"` |\n\n### Implementation highlights\n\n- `geo({ headers })` and `geoFromHeaders(headers)` follow the exact same split as `userAgent`/`userAgentFromString`\n- Header priority: Vercel `x-vercel-ip-*` first; Cloudflare `cf-ipcountry` as fallback for `countryCode` only\n- `country` derived from `countryCode` via a `COUNTRY_NAMES` map (10 entries: AU, BR, CA, CN, DE, FR, GB, IN, JP, US)\n- `isInRegion` does case-insensitive country code comparison\n- `geoDistance` uses the Haversine formula returning km\n- `null` â†’ `undefined` coercion via `?? undefined` for clean strict TypeScript typing",
